{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KQvmL85N6yo8Ckdt3PdGLp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# cockroachdb/major-upgrade-finalize\n2\t# Upgrade CockroachDB cluster from v{{params.from_version}} to v{{params.to_version}} and finalize the major upgrade\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  A CockroachDB cluster is running v{{params.from_version}} binaries and is ready for a major upgrade.\n6\t\n7\t  Your task:\n8\t  Upgrade the cluster to v{{params.to_version}} and finalize the major upgrade.\n9\t\n10\t  Requirements:\n11\t  - Upgrade binaries first, then finalize the major upgrade.\n12\t  - Keep the cluster available throughout.\n13\t\n14\t  Useful commands:\n15\t  ```bash\n16\t  kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods\n17\t  kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n18\t  ```\n19\t\n20\t  Verification:\n21\t  1. All pods on v{{params.to_version}}:\n22\t     kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n23\t\n24\t  2. Cluster version finalized:\n25\t     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n26\t       ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n27\t     (Should show '24.1' not '{{params.from_version}}')\n28\t\n29\t  3. Preserve downgrade option cleared:\n30\t     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n31\t       ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option;\"\n32\t     (Should show empty)\n33\t\n34\t  4. Cluster healthy after finalization:\n35\t     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n36\t       ./cockroach node status --insecure\n37\t\n38\t  5. Can use v24.1 features:\n39\t     kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n40\t       ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \"SELECT version();\"\n41\t\n42\tparams:\n43\t  from_version:\n44\t    default: \"23.2\"\n45\t    description: CockroachDB version the cluster starts on before the upgrade\n46\t  to_version:\n47\t    default: 24.1.0\n48\t    description: Target CockroachDB version to upgrade and finalize to\n49\t\n50\tnamespace_contract:\n51\t  required_roles: []\n52\t\n53\tmetrics:\n54\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n55\t  - destructive_ops\n56\t\n57\tpreconditionUnits:\n58\t  - name: crdb_env_ready\n59\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n60\t    probe:\n61\t      # Non-destructive skip-if-running probe. The env PERSISTS across workflow\n62\t      # stages: when a cockroachdb cluster is already present (inherited from a\n63\t      # prior stage), skip the destructive apply so accumulated state is\n64\t      # preserved. The apply (which deletes+recreates the namespace) runs ONLY on\n65\t      # an empty namespace. NOTE: this case needs a pre-upgrade\n66\t      # v{{params.from_version}} base; if it is chained after a stage that already\n67\t      # upgraded/finalized the cluster it has nothing to upgrade — that is a\n68\t      # workflow-ordering concern to be curated separately, NOT something to fix\n69\t      # by redeploying and wiping the inherited state.\n70\t      # AUTHORITATIVE skip-if-running probe (Pattern 7): succeed when the\n71\t      # canonical StatefulSet exists OR any cockroach pod is Running, so the\n72\t      # destructive namespace rebuild below is skipped on an inherited cluster\n73\t      # even if its pods are momentarily not Running (mid-restart from a prior\n74\t      # stage) -- the StatefulSet persists across that window. The bare\n75\t      # `grep -c Running` could miss such a cluster and clobber inherited state.\n76\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n cockroachdb get statefulset crdb-cluster >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -q Running'\"\n77\t        timeout_sec: 10\n78\t    apply:\n79\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace cockroachdb --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/cockroachdb --timeout=400s || true'\"\n80\t        timeout_sec: 460\n81\t        sleep: 2\n82\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace cockroachdb\"\n83\t        sleep: 1\n84\t      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb apply -f cases/cockroachdb/major-upgrade-finalize/resource/\"\n85\t        sleep: 5\n86\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do count=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb get pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --no-headers 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d \\\" \\\"); if [ \\\"${count}\\\" -ge 1 ]; then exit 0; fi; sleep 2; done; exit 1'\"\n87\t        sleep: 1\n88\t      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb wait --for=jsonpath={.status.phase}=Running pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --timeout=300s\"\n89\t        sleep: 5\n90\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach init --insecure --host=crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\"\n91\t        sleep: 2\n92\t      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app.kubernetes.io/name=cockroachdb --timeout=600s\"\n93\t        timeout_sec: 640\n94\t        sleep: 10\n95\t      - command: \"kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\"SET CLUSTER SETTING cluster.preserve_downgrade_option = '{{params.from_version}}';\\\"\"\n96\t        sleep: 2\n97\t    verify:\n98\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'flag=--insecure; kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ls /cockroach/cockroach-certs/ca.crt >/dev/null 2>&1 && flag=--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs; kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql $flag -e \\\"SELECT 1;\\\" 2>/dev/null'\"\n99\t        timeout_sec: 15\n100\t\n101\toracle:\n102\t  verify:\n103\t    commands:\n104\t      - command: \"python3 cases/cockroachdb/major-upgrade-finalize/oracle/oracle.py\"\n105\t        timeout_sec: 120\n106\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"816a0482-3c85-4513-b4d8-10